story.text: Woke up midway through the night with a tickle in my throat - a little less severe in the morning. Not sure why - I have been sleeping well. But alas, the body is a mystery.

I think things are going well with my life. I am happy with the progress of life. With my job - and with the prospects that lie ahead. With New Shape, Tippet, Red Lodge, Stillwater, and the legal field.
If love is the answer, then love is the answer. I hope that I love humans as much as I love humanity. I hope that I love humanity as much as I love the survival of humanity.
